  "doc_id": "22524",
  "text": "The function of cytochrome P450 (CYP) enzymes varies by enzyme species, but many are involved in drug metabolism. Genetic mutations are known to occur in CYP2C19 and in CYP2C9, [CITATION_1] and as a result, drug metabolizing capacity is markedly lowered in poor metabolizers (PMs), leading to increases in blood concentration and the occurrence of side effects. [CITATION_2] Ethnic differences exist, and a higher frequency of CYP2C19 1 (PM genotype, 11.7-25.7%) has been reported in Asian populations compared with other populations.",
